Pop a large #frying pan{} or #wok{} on a medium high heat. When hot, add the @Cooked Pulled Chicken{200%g} and cook stirring occasionally until piping hot, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the @Pak Choi{1} then thinly slice widthways.

Finely chop the @Salted Peanuts{40%g} or crush them with the base of a pan.

Once the chicken is piping hot, add the bok choy and @Chilli Flakes{1%tsp}, stir fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Udon Noodles{300%g}, @Sriracha Sauce{1%tbsp}, @Szechuan Paste{75%g}, @Soy Sauce{25%g} and @Water{75%ml}.

Break the noodles up as you stir them through, ensuring they are fully coated with sauce and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Whilst the sauce and noodles cook, finely chop the @Coriander{1}(stalks and all) and trim the @Spring Onion{2} and finely slice.

Once the noodles have softened, share them between your bowls.

Sprinkle over the spring onion, coriander and peanuts. Enjoy!